    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n7307" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πᾶς, πᾶσα, πᾶν</span></b> , pl. gen. fem.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πᾱσέων, πᾱσά̄ων</span>, dat. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάντεσσι</span>: sing., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">every</span>
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">one</span>), <i><span class="en">Il. 16.265</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 13.313</span></i>; pl.,
          <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">all</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐννέα πάντες</span>, nine
          ‘in all,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 7.161</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 8.258</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">whole, entire</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 2.809</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.549</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">all sorts, all kinds</span>, in pl.,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 1.5</span></i>, etc.—Neut. pl. as adv.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πάντα</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">in all
            respects</span>, in the Iliad mostly in comparisons, but in the
          Odyssey only so in <i><span class="en">Od. 24.446</span></i>;
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">all over</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 16.21</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 17.480</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
